title: The Hippo Supremacy
subTitle: Zambia's Luangwa River hippos are living the easy life, or so it seems. They are one of the heaviest creatures on Earth, and life fluctuates between the serenity of sunbathing and the terrible brutality of dominance and aggression.

title: The new animal kingdom Japan
subTitle: A young fox tries to find a new territory on the island of Honshu in Japan. Along the way, he encounters a variety of animals trying to adapt to an ever-changing environment.

title: The Lions Rule
subTitle: During the dry season in Ruaha state, a herd of elephants visit the water body at Glade to extract the cleanest water using their trunks.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: In the heart of Zululand, South Africa, lies the oldest game reserve on the African continent.

title: Wild Africa: Rivers of Life
subTitle: On the Luangwa River, the law of the land is dictated by the ever-changing seasons and the constant cycle of life. In the wet season the Luangwa Valley is a green paradise, as the waters flow in abundance and lush green vegetation carpets the landscape. But in the dry season, when rains become but a distant memory, the greenery turns brown and the water levels drop by a foot per day.

title: A Wild Year On Earth
subTitle: Rain welcomes baby meerkats to the Kalahari. The arrival spring in eastern Australia ignites the passions everything from kangaroos to humpback whales.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: The Taiga, the world's largest forest, occupies the northern regions of North America, Europe and Asia and is inhabited by bears, wolverines, wolves and moose.

title: Animal Arms Race
subTitle: In this big blue battleground, every creature has its own array of weapons for finding prey or avoiding becoming prey themselves.

title: Islands: Nature's Wild Laboratories
subTitle: The sandy island of K'Gari, formerly Fraser Island, stretches off the east coast of Australia.

title: Arabian Inferno
subTitle: A wadi is a waterhole, a rare place in the desert where hard bedrock traps the tiniest traces of water. A vital valley visited by the creepy and bizarre. All animals must come here to drink, something predators are quick to exploit; venomous vipers, glowing scorpions and stalking tarantulas hide in the crevices, ever ready to strike.

title: Wildest Survival
subTitle: No animals are as resilient as those who live in the coldest climes. We'll reveal the surprising adaptations earth's cold weather creatures have evolved to survive.

title: The Lions Rule
subTitle: The Glade is a paradise in the desiccated plains of Ruaha, where water is available year round. This bounty spawns strange relationships. But peace in the Glade is shattered when thousands of buffalo arrive to drink, followed by the Baobab pride.

title: Kanga Pan: An African Horror Story
subTitle: At a relatively unknown inland waterhole in Mana Pools National Park, a baboon begins to notice that various animals are going missing. He makes it his mission to uncover the cause.

title: Survive the Wild
subTitle: From microscopic single celled organisms to the largest animals on the planet, one goal is shared by all living things: to reproduce. For many creatures, finding a suitable mate to pass on strong genes and rear young that will survive to adulthood is a challenge that is met with a variety of strategies. In this episode we will observe the creative tactics animals employ to find the best mates and to win them over.

title: Nature's Ultimate Survivors
subTitle: The crew explore innovative parenting strategies in animals that these species employ to protect their offspring.

subTitle: The team travels to the vast continent of North America to follow the long-running battle between wolves and musk oxen; they also get to see how porpoises hunt for fish.

title: Chasing the Rains

title: Nature's Fast Attacks
subTitle: Showcasing how the world's fastest predators can strike and kill in the blink of an eye, using modern high-speed cameras to capture these lightning-fast attacks in deadly detail.

subTitle: The surprising ways animals have adapted to ensure they make it to old age.

title: Brotherhood of Lions
subTitle: While the lion cubs at the Masai Mara Reserve prey on buffalo, one of them emerges to assert themselves as the dominant leader to guide the pride in attacking their victim.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Wild Sky
subTitle: Examining the Amazon rainforest's oxygen-breathing trees and meeting flamingos that thrive in the sun's scorching UV rays.

title: Wild Africa: Rivers of Life
subTitle: For four months of the year, the powerful Limpopo river revitalises the landscape, nourishing the abundance of wildlife dependent on it. For the remaining seven months its waters are locked away in inaccessible underground aquifers, leaving behind a series of small and ever-shrinking muddy pools. Excruciating heat and drought ravage the area until the next rains.
